1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,320
 You know, when we go on sabbatical, we're told to rest, retreat, revive, and to return.

2
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:08,960
 So they're like, "Do come back.

3
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:13,400
 You have time to think about everything, but we want you to come back."

4
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,960
 And so it's so good to be back.

5
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:18,640
 I was back last week, but now I'm back preaching this week.

6
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:21,560
 And yeah, I missed you, and I'm happy to be back.

7
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:23,560
 So that's a good thing, right?

8
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:27,000
 And also, I want to just give a shout out to my team.

9
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,200
 I'm so proud of them.

10
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,920
 They did such a wonderful job in my absence.

11
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:34,520
 It's like, basically, I'm not needed, you know?

12
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:37,720
 But I think it really just speaks of them, you know?

13
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:40,000
 And so I'm just grateful.

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,840
 And I want to give a special shout out to Pastor Ivan on that, who took on the leadership

15
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,360
 role and kind of oversaw the team.

16
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:46,360
 And he's not here.

17
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:47,360
 He's on vacation.

18
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:50,480
 He needed a vacation from my sabbatical.

19
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:52,120
 But so yeah, that's good.

20
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:58,240
 But anyhow, I want to share with you from 2018 something I experienced.

21
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:06,280
 I was flying with my German friend, Matthias, from Hong Kong to Tel Aviv, Israel.

22
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:10,400
 And usually when I'm on a flight, I'm super uncomfortable.

23
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,600
 There's a reason for it.

24
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:18,720
 I'm a tall guy, and I don't really fit good into the economy seats.

25
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:20,400
 That's usually where I sit.

26
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:24,720
 And my knees, they jam into the front, the seat in front of me.

27
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:29,080
 Sometimes, depending on what seat, the side might press on me as well.

28
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,560
 I can't stretch out my legs.

29
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:33,400
 I have to kind of weirdly contort them.

30
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,280
 And so I hate flying.

31
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:38,320
 I love getting to the destinations, but I hate flying.

32
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:44,760
 And so what I try to do is watch movies so I can forget about what's going on.

33
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:50,320
 Hopefully, they have good movies that will distract me, make that flight pass by faster.

34
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:55,240
 And I've even for a while, though I didn't have that recently, have had anxieties actually

35
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,800
 about flying.

36
00:01:56,800 --> 00:02:00,320
 And it's not because I'm scared that the plane is going to crash.

37
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,560
 It's because I'm scared of sitting in the seat.

38
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,560
 You know?

39
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,560
 And so for me, this is a big deal.

40
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:10,760
 So here I am on my flight to Tel Aviv.

41
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:16,160
 You know what I usually do, but this time was different.

42
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:19,920
 And it's something I've never experienced before.

43
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:28,200
 I had this deep longing, but also just an awareness of a deep need in my life that I

44
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:35,200
 needed to draw close to Jesus, that I needed more of the presence of the Holy Spirit in

45
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,620
 my life.

46
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:42,240
 And so instead of watching movies, I plugged in my earphones and I was worshipping and

47
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:48,240
 I was praying the entire flight, which was like 10 hours or something like that.

48
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:54,640
 Now, I know I'm a pastor, but I don't usually pray and worship for 10 hours on a flight.

49
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:57,680
 I might do that for half an hour, maybe an hour.

50
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:01,800
 You know, so this is not my normal behavior.

51
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:05,540
 But there was just something really that God was doing.

52
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:08,840
 And I said yes to it, because I know I needed it.

53
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:14,320
 And so the best way I know how to explain it is like, I had just been, or actually I

54
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:22,560
 still was in the most difficult season of my life, where there was incredible pain of

55
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:26,280
 loss of relationship, job, home.

56
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:29,360
 There was disorientation.

57
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,640
 And I was just coming out of that.

58
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,800
 Jesus had met me.

59
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,120
 I had no way forward.

60
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:37,360
 He met me, helped me get out of a place where I was stuck.

61
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:43,520
 But I was still in need for him to do healing work in my life.

62
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:47,600
 I was still in need for more of his presence.

63
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:55,440
 Now, I wonder about you, if you experience the same thing or something similar that I

64
00:03:55,440 --> 00:04:01,400
 experienced, where there is just an awareness of or longing that you're carrying, that you're

65
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:06,920
 holding, where you just know, man, I need God to work in this part of my life.

66
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:13,280
 I need a greater presence of the Holy Spirit in my life.

67
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:16,320
 I just desperately need it.

68
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:24,280
 For me, it was because there was brokenness, there was grieving, and no one could comfort

69
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,280
 me.

70
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:30,000
 My family, they loved me, but they couldn't comfort me.

71
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,520
 So I knew I needed to draw close to God.

72
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:35,920
 For you, maybe there's a need for forgiveness.

73
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:41,400
 Like sometimes we're just stuck in a mess, and we know what we're doing is wrong, and

74
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,880
 for whatever reason we can't stop it, and we just need Jesus.

75
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:46,360
 I need forgiveness.

76
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:50,600
 I need a greater holiness in my life.

77
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:56,560
 Like wholeness, not like holier than thou, but like just wholeness.

78
00:04:56,560 --> 00:05:01,280
 Because there's just pain, there's brokenness, and I'm just doing things I don't want to

79
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,280
 do.

80
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:03,280
 Maybe there's addiction.

81
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,760
 We can be addicted to all sorts of things.

82
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:10,200
 Maybe it's addiction to the one that I wonder whether or not I'm addicted to, social media.

83
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:13,440
 Maybe there's social media addiction.

84
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:16,640
 Maybe there's addiction to alcohol.

85
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:22,360
 We like to drink alcohol when we have problems to kind of comfort our pain or take the edge

86
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:25,200
 off, you know, a tough day at work.

87
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,080
 Maybe there's addiction to pornography.

88
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:33,560
 Maybe there's addiction to your work, where you just can't stop working, even if it costs

89
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:36,800
 your family and your friends.

90
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:43,560
 And there is a need for freedom, for deliverance from oppression, for God to do something new,

91
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:47,460
 for the Holy Spirit to move in your life.

92
00:05:47,460 --> 00:05:52,600
 Maybe there's a need for direction, where you're like, "I know that what I'm doing is

93
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:56,640
 not what God has for me, not who God created me to be, but I don't know what the purpose

94
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,640
 of my life is."

95
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:02,880
 And there's just a longing, "God, just can you just show me what your purpose for me

96
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:05,680
 is, what you have for me?"

97
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,080
 So it can be all sorts of things.

98
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:08,080
 You can fill in the blank.

99
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:15,320
 You know what need, what longing you're sitting with.

100
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,320
 You know that.

101
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:26,400
 And so what I want to do today with this message, I want to actually, for us to ask a question,

102
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:32,580
 and it's this question, what is that longing or need that you are carrying in your life

103
00:06:32,580 --> 00:06:37,640
 right now where you need Jesus to meet you?

104
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:46,680
 Where you need a greater sense of his presence?

105
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,360
 Where do you need him?

106
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:54,640
 And so today we're taking a break from the Daniel sermon series for one week.

107
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,640
 Sorry.

108
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:59,580
 We're going to return to that next week.

109
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:08,160
 But I want to take you to the Gospel of John, and I want to set the scene for us.

110
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:11,640
 So it's the Feast of Tabernacles.

111
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:18,520
 It's one of the three great feasts in Judaism, and there is a buzz in the city of Jerusalem.

112
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:23,160
 There's people from all, even other nations, you know, coming to the Jewish diaspora, they're

113
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:29,720
 journeying to Jerusalem to celebrate this joyous feast, but there's also some tension

114
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:37,820
 in the air, and that tension revolves around Jesus.

115
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:41,640
 People are divided over his identity.

116
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,720
 Is he the Messiah?

117
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:49,040
 Is he the one that we're longing for and waiting for as a nation to bring deliverance, to do

118
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,520
 something new?

119
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:58,200
 Or is he a false teacher?

120
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:02,440
 As a matter of fact, some people did think he was a false teacher, and they were planning

121
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:05,060
 on killing him.

122
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:14,040
 So this is the atmosphere that's happening, and into this atmosphere, Jesus stands up

123
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:22,680
 and he has some words to speak that still matter to us today, that still speak to us

124
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,680
 today.

125
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,720
 So let me take you there.

126
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,920
 We're in John chapter 7.

127
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:30,000
 We're starting in verse 37.

128
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:40,360
 It says this, "On the last and greatest day of the festival, Jesus stood and said in a

129
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:46,040
 loud voice, 'Let anyone who is thirsty come to me and drink.

130
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:53,240
 Whoever believes in me, as scripture has said, rivers of living water will flow from within

131
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,600
 them.'

132
00:08:55,600 --> 00:09:01,880
 But this he meant the spirit, whom those who believed in him were later to receive.

133
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:09,920
 Up to that time, the spirit had not been given, since Jesus had not yet been glorified."

134
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:13,920
 And hearing his words, some of the people said, "Surely this man is the prophet."

135
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:17,720
 Others said, "He's the Messiah."

136
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:21,000
 Still others asked, "How can the Messiah come from Galilee?

137
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:29,720
 Does not scripture say that the Messiah will be David's descendant from Bethlehem, the

138
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:32,000
 town where David lived?"

139
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:36,200
 Thus the people were divided because of Jesus.

140
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:41,280
 No one wanted to seize him, but no one laid a hand on him.

141
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:44,400
 So right, let's unpack this passage.

142
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:49,960
 It says that all of this is happening on the last and the greatest day of the Feast of

143
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,960
 Tabernacles.

144
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:55,680
 It's also sometimes called the Feast of Booth, so it has both names.

145
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,680
 Now what was this feast about?

146
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:03,120
 Well, I want to highlight one ceremony from that feast, and it was a water drawing ceremony.

147
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:09,640
 So the priests, they came from the temple, they went to Siloam, a pool, they got water,

148
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:14,160
 there was a procedure back, there's psalms being sung, there's scriptures read, and then

149
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:21,080
 they went around the altar and they poured, as worship, they poured water on the altar.

150
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:26,480
 And this ceremony and the symbolism of it was looking back, but it was also looking

151
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,480
 forward.

152
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:35,240
 It was looking back on Israel's wandering in the desert during the Exodus time, when

153
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:41,440
 they were dying, or they thought they were dying of thirst, and they're complaining,

154
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:44,360
 "Why did you lead us out of Egypt?

155
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:47,480
 Now we're just here and we're dying of thirst."

156
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:55,960
 So God told Moses to take the rod, to strike the rock, and out came gushing water, living

157
00:10:55,960 --> 00:11:01,040
 water, and it saved the thirsty people.

158
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,200
 It was a deliverance.

159
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,520
 So they're celebrating this.

160
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:09,680
 They're celebrating this important occasion in their community's life.

161
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:16,800
 But they're also looking forward, because the prophets had been talking about a time

162
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:23,160
 when there would be waters flowing from Jerusalem, there would be waters flowing from the temple,

163
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:29,200
 and they would be watering the land, there would be a work of renewal, of restoration,

164
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,960
 of healing.

165
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:34,640
 Whatever the river touches brings life.

166
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,680
 So there's all sorts of scriptures.

167
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:43,240
 There's an Isaiah in Joel, and Ezekiel, and in Zechariah.

168
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:47,000
 And I want to read to you just one little verse from Zechariah that probably was read

169
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,320
 even during this festival.

170
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:55,840
 And it's from Zechariah 14, verse 8, and it says this, "On that day, living water will

171
00:11:55,840 --> 00:12:01,720
 flow out from Jerusalem, half of it east to the Dead Sea, and half of it west to the Mediterranean

172
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:06,640
 Sea, in summer and in winter."

173
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:11,760
 So again, there's this symbolism in a place where there's not much water, of water flowing

174
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:18,720
 regularly and flowing in all directions, and bringing life and doing something new on that

175
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:25,200
 day, on that day when God acts decisively.

176
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:31,440
 And so there's this anticipation in this festival for the people, there's their longings.

177
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:36,080
 It's a nation that is longing for God to move in a greater and a more powerful way, and

178
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:44,060
 to bring restoration, to bring healing to a land, to a people that is hurting.

179
00:12:44,060 --> 00:12:50,560
 And so this is what this watery ceremony on the Feast of Tamil Water expresses.

180
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:56,040
 This powerful symbolism, this celebration of God's deliverance, but also this looking ahead

181
00:12:56,040 --> 00:13:01,840
 to this messianic time where God will act in a decisive way.

182
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:08,600
 And on the last day of the festival, the greatest day, they did the seven times.

183
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:17,760
 So imagine the seven times coming to end, they're pouring the water on the altar, and

184
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:22,620
 there's these expectations that people are holding, there's this longing from the people,

185
00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:29,460
 and Jesus stands up, and he says in a loud voice, actually it can also be translated,

186
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:37,000
 he cried out, "Let anyone who's thirsty come to me and drink.

187
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:41,580
 Whoever believes in me, as scripture has said, rivers of living water will flow from within

188
00:13:41,580 --> 00:13:44,860
 them."

189
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:51,260
 Now I don't know about you, but I wish I could have been there that day.

190
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:58,900
 I could have been in that crowd, I could have been there at this moment.

191
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:07,180
 Jesus was saying, "That longing that you're expressing through this festival, I am the

192
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:09,240
 fulfillment of that.

193
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:14,220
 The thirst that you're experiencing where you need God to meet you, I am the one who

194
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:17,020
 can meet that thirst.

195
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:24,420
 The Messiah that you're waiting for, it's me.

196
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:26,940
 I am the fulfillment of this festival.

197
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:34,820
 I am the one who can truly quench this thirst that nothing else has been able to quench."

198
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:37,700
 Now just think about this.

199
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:42,780
 What a weighty statement for anyone to make.

200
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:45,900
 But of course Jesus is not anyone.

201
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:50,420
 He is the son of God who can truly quench our thirst.

202
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:55,380
 And we can see that people understood what he was saying by the way they're processing

203
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:59,820
 what Jesus just has declared and invited people into.

204
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:07,980
 So we can look at verse 40 through 44.

205
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:11,500
 There it talks about all these different reactions, right?

206
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,420
 He's a prophet, he's a Messiah.

207
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:18,780
 I don't think he can be the Messiah because he wasn't born and he's from Nazareth.

208
00:15:18,780 --> 00:15:21,460
 They didn't know he was actually born in Bethlehem.

209
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:24,740
 Or they want to arrest him.

210
00:15:24,740 --> 00:15:30,220
 I mean, that is a strong reaction to words that somebody speaks.

211
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:33,540
 But it's because they are so weighty.

212
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:38,660
 Because what Jesus says is so profound.

213
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:42,380
 And Jesus' invitation still stands today.

214
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:46,780
 Let anyone who is thirsty come to me.

215
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:52,560
 It doesn't say let those who have their lives together come to me.

216
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:57,700
 It doesn't say that those who are living good moral lives and are being good little people

217
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:59,100
 come to me.

218
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:02,660
 You know, anyone who thirsts.

219
00:16:02,660 --> 00:16:07,700
 So the requirements basically just acknowledging you have a need.

220
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:15,460
 There's a desperation in your heart and your life for Jesus to meet you.

221
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:20,460
 For a cup of water, for a drink.

222
00:16:20,460 --> 00:16:22,540
 That's it.

223
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:25,380
 But sometimes the simple things, they sound so simple.

224
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:29,160
 Oh yeah, you just admit your need and you get a drink.

225
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:33,800
 But they're not that simple for us a lot of times, right?

226
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:43,360
 For me, as we were planting the church, it was before we started having any services,

227
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:47,140
 I was playing down some sin in my life.

228
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:50,700
 Just like, "Oh, it's not a big deal.

229
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:53,820
 Everybody would think this is an issue, blah, blah, blah."

230
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:56,180
 So basically I'm deceiving myself.

231
00:16:56,180 --> 00:16:59,820
 I'm just like, "Oh, you know, I don't have a need.

232
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,740
 I'm okay."

233
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:05,740
 So we can deceive ourselves about our thirst.

234
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:08,460
 And I actually had to confess my sin.

235
00:17:08,460 --> 00:17:10,780
 Say, "Jesus, will you come in this area of my life?

236
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:13,300
 Will you help me to clean this up?

237
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:15,180
 Because I need you.

238
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:16,180
 I need your mercy.

239
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:18,940
 I need your grace in this area of my life."

240
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:25,540
 And actually I knew that God was preparing me to pastor you all, but that something needed

241
00:17:25,540 --> 00:17:26,540
 to be sorted out.

242
00:17:26,540 --> 00:17:27,540
 Now, no pastor's perfect.

243
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:31,940
 There's still sin and issues in my life, like every person.

244
00:17:31,940 --> 00:17:35,260
 But it was something that God wanted me to sort out, and I had to admit it.

245
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:38,660
 I had to admit that I'm thirsty, that I'm needy.

246
00:17:38,660 --> 00:17:44,700
 So a lot of times we're prideful or we're in denial and we don't want to admit it.

247
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:47,580
 So that's the first thing that kind of hinders us from actually coming to Jesus.

248
00:17:47,580 --> 00:17:50,380
 Just saying, "Jesus, I need you."

249
00:17:50,380 --> 00:17:56,700
 The second thing is that we actually really struggle to believe that Jesus is the one

250
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:59,280
 who can quench our thirst.

251
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:03,400
 We think that there's other things who can quench our thirst.

252
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:13,420
 We think that if only I had more money, if I had a relationship, if I would achieve greater

253
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:18,220
 things, then this thirst would be quenched in my life.

254
00:18:18,220 --> 00:18:22,900
 If only I had more money, I would have peace of mind, I wouldn't have to have anxiety.

255
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:28,240
 If only I was in this relationship, I would finally feel whole, because I'm somewhat feeling

256
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,760
 not 100% right.

257
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:36,540
 If only I would achieve more and I would reach this position, then people would accept me,

258
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:39,940
 would love me.

259
00:18:39,940 --> 00:18:43,860
 So we believe what surrounding culture tells us and models to us.

260
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:50,220
 And we believe that over that Jesus is the source of living water who can truly quench

261
00:18:50,220 --> 00:18:51,220
 our thirst.

262
00:18:51,220 --> 00:18:53,260
 Now these other things, they can do a little something for us.

263
00:18:53,260 --> 00:18:56,260
 It's not like they don't do anything.

264
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,260
 That's not true.

265
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:59,220
 But they never fully deliver.

266
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:04,340
 They always leave us hanging dry.

267
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:07,340
 And even as Christians, we struggle to believe that.

268
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:14,220
 We believe in those other things, but we don't or not always believe that Jesus is the one

269
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:20,620
 that can actually quench our thirst.

270
00:19:20,620 --> 00:19:28,860
 So if you want change and transformation in your life, if you want your thirst to be quenched,

271
00:19:28,860 --> 00:19:33,900
 you have to admit that you have a thirst.

272
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:41,420
 Jesus is inviting anyone who is thirsty to come to him.

273
00:19:41,420 --> 00:19:43,100
 But we have to admit it.

274
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:48,860
 We have to bring it to him, not think we can deal with it on our own or think something

275
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:54,340
 else will fulfill that.

276
00:19:54,340 --> 00:20:04,740
 Now drinking the water is actually believing or trusting in Jesus.

277
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:09,060
 Now a lot of times we think of belief, trust, faith.

278
00:20:09,060 --> 00:20:13,020
 We think of this like perfect, you know, we need to have this perfectly when I come to

279
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:14,260
 Jesus.

280
00:20:14,260 --> 00:20:17,180
 But actually Jesus can work with very little.

281
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:20,300
 If you come and you pray to him, that actually is an act of faith.

282
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:22,180
 That actually is an act of trust.

283
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:23,780
 And he will meet you.

284
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:33,180
 He will work in your life when you bring whatever is going on to him.

285
00:20:33,180 --> 00:20:40,580
 Now in verse 39, John, the gospel writer, he explains a little bit more of what he says.

286
00:20:40,580 --> 00:20:46,940
 He says, "But this he meant the Spirit, whom those who believed in him were later to receive.

287
00:20:46,940 --> 00:20:52,180
 Up to that time the Spirit had not been given, since Jesus had not yet been glorified."

288
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:56,500
 So the first thing is when it talks about this water, it's talking about the Holy Spirit

289
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:58,620
 that Jesus gives us to drink.

290
00:20:58,620 --> 00:21:02,380
 You know, it's a Spirit, the Holy Spirit that we receive when we believe, when we repent

291
00:21:02,380 --> 00:21:05,700
 of our sins, we place our trust in him, and we become Christians.

292
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:08,620
 The Spirit, the Holy Spirit lives within us.

293
00:21:08,620 --> 00:21:10,220
 We are his children.

294
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:13,980
 We cross over from death to life, we're born again.

295
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:17,300
 You know, that's what this is talking about.

296
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:25,660
 But it also is talking about, you know, Jesus, he loves pouring out his Spirit into our lives.

297
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:31,100
 And the Bible talks about the filling of the Holy Spirit, you know, that we can have an

298
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:34,700
 experience of presence of the Holy Spirit in greater measure.

299
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:41,220
 So it's like both of these things is what's going on here.

300
00:21:41,220 --> 00:21:46,020
 But a lot of times, so this passage, you know, one of the main focuses is salvation.

301
00:21:46,020 --> 00:21:48,460
 It's becoming a Christian.

302
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:52,660
 And then if you have not done that, this is really the most important step for you to

303
00:21:52,660 --> 00:21:53,660
 take.

304
00:21:53,660 --> 00:21:57,780
 You know, and the way we become a Christian, there's two things that the New Testament

305
00:21:57,780 --> 00:21:58,780
 talks about.

306
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:00,960
 It's repentance and it's faith.

307
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:05,940
 Repentance means I say, "Jesus, I am sorry for sinning against you, for hurting other

308
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:07,620
 people.

309
00:22:07,620 --> 00:22:09,740
 Will you forgive me?"

310
00:22:09,740 --> 00:22:12,580
 And then the second thing is, you know, faith.

311
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:14,540
 So, "Jesus, I trust you.

312
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:15,820
 Will you come into my life?

313
00:22:15,820 --> 00:22:23,500
 Will you fill me with your Spirit and teach me what it means to now live for you?"

314
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:26,880
 And so this is the invitation.

315
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:30,620
 But there is a second aspect in this text as well.

316
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:36,980
 And we see that in verse 38.

317
00:22:36,980 --> 00:22:40,860
 And a lot of times, you know, when we preach on these texts, we stop at becoming a Christian.

318
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:43,780
 But I want to also talk about this other part.

319
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:49,060
 And it says that rivers of living water will flow from within them.

320
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:53,780
 You know, when we become a Christian, the Holy Spirit is poured out on us.

321
00:22:53,780 --> 00:22:57,700
 And it's described as rivers of living water flowing from within them.

322
00:22:57,700 --> 00:22:59,020
 So it means it flows out.

323
00:22:59,020 --> 00:23:02,100
 It doesn't stay where it is.

324
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:06,220
 And this is not something that happens, you know, this is a one-time thing.

325
00:23:06,220 --> 00:23:09,620
 This is an ongoing thing.

326
00:23:09,620 --> 00:23:17,980
 But I wonder, you know, are there rivers of living water right now flowing from within

327
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:18,980
 your life?

328
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:22,860
 Is the Holy Spirit bubbling over in your life?

329
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:27,900
 You know, because a lot of times I think it's like a little trickle.

330
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:30,100
 It's not rivers of living water.

331
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:36,740
 It's like a little trickle.

332
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:46,180
 You know, but Jesus, He pours out His Spirit, you know, so that we can be a blessing to

333
00:23:46,180 --> 00:23:47,180
 others.

334
00:23:47,180 --> 00:23:50,460
 So whatever God does to work in our lives, yes, it is to meet our needs.

335
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:52,020
 And He cares about our needs.

336
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:54,740
 And He will meet them and He will provide.

337
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:56,940
 But it always also goes beyond that.

338
00:23:56,940 --> 00:24:01,180
 That because of this work that He does in our lives, it will bubble over, it will flow

339
00:24:01,180 --> 00:24:04,540
 over to touch other people's lives.

340
00:24:04,540 --> 00:24:07,980
 And so here's an important truth.

341
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:11,060
 Revived lives revive others.

342
00:24:11,060 --> 00:24:19,140
 You know, if your life is revived, it will revive others.

343
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:24,980
 Jesus doesn't want His goodness to stop with us.

344
00:24:24,980 --> 00:24:27,980
 He doesn't want His goodness to find a dead end in us.

345
00:24:27,980 --> 00:24:34,420
 He wants it to flow through us.

346
00:24:34,420 --> 00:24:40,220
 He wants rivers of living water stirring within us.

347
00:24:40,220 --> 00:24:46,860
 Yes, meeting us in our needs, giving us the grace, the mercy, the strength, the comfort,

348
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:48,940
 the love, whatever it is we need.

349
00:24:48,940 --> 00:24:55,580
 But He also wants to work and flow through you.

350
00:24:55,580 --> 00:25:01,340
 So Jesus, not only does He give us this living water, give us the Spirit when we become a

351
00:25:01,340 --> 00:25:09,460
 Christian, but He loves pouring out His Spirit as we are followers of Jesus in an ongoing

352
00:25:09,460 --> 00:25:10,460
 way.

353
00:25:10,460 --> 00:25:11,460
 And we can ask Him for it.

354
00:25:11,460 --> 00:25:12,460
 He loves doing it.

355
00:25:12,460 --> 00:25:13,460
 He loves doing it.

356
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:20,380
 Now, earlier I actually didn't finish my story of riding in the plane.

357
00:25:20,380 --> 00:25:23,660
 I had this longing, I had this desire of more of Jesus.

358
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:27,540
 I'm worshiping in this really uncomfortable space, but I forgot about that.

359
00:25:27,540 --> 00:25:33,420
 And that actually continued when I was in Israel, like in the mornings, in the evenings.

360
00:25:33,420 --> 00:25:37,740
 I love that time of worship, of prayer, of reading Scripture.

361
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:39,100
 And then when I came back, it also continued.

362
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:45,820
 It was just this longing and this need for the presence of the Holy Spirit, for Jesus

363
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:47,940
 to meet me.

364
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:51,820
 And so I was at home, I was reading a book that an acquaintance of mine wrote, and she

365
00:25:51,820 --> 00:25:54,860
 writes a book on prayer, and writes about the Holy Spirit and prayer.

366
00:25:54,860 --> 00:26:00,300
 And so as I was reading this, I'm sitting in the room in quietness, and the Holy Spirit

367
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:04,540
 just poured out over me in a way I hadn't experienced before.

368
00:26:04,540 --> 00:26:11,860
 And just a great sense of His love, and there was just a deep awareness of His presence

369
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:14,820
 and also of His healing work.

370
00:26:14,820 --> 00:26:16,340
 And it was really special, really personal.

371
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:19,460
 I'm also not sharing all the details.

372
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:29,780
 And it's easy to highlight these moments, these mountaintop moments.

373
00:26:29,780 --> 00:26:32,100
 That was a mountaintop moment for me.

374
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:37,020
 But actually, what I was going through was a season.

375
00:26:37,020 --> 00:26:42,220
 Because it was a whole season where the Holy Spirit was working and renewing my heart,

376
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:47,540
 and bringing comfort and healing to brokenness.

377
00:26:47,540 --> 00:26:54,620
 And honestly, after what I experienced, it was trauma, because I didn't see it coming.

378
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:56,660
 It was unexpected.

379
00:26:56,660 --> 00:27:01,540
 And so there were things that were triggering me, where I can be in a conversation with

380
00:27:01,540 --> 00:27:05,060
 something and somehow something gets triggered, and I'm starting to feel physical pain in

381
00:27:05,060 --> 00:27:09,860
 my body, and I know in my mind it doesn't make any sense, but I'm experiencing it.

382
00:27:09,860 --> 00:27:12,820
 You know, and I'm shaking up, and I can't even function normally.

383
00:27:12,820 --> 00:27:16,020
 I mean, that's when I first came to the Vine, that's where I was at.

384
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:18,420
 That's what I was experiencing.

385
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:25,020
 You know, but Jesus, and in the presence of the Holy Spirit, He healed that trauma.

386
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:27,700
 You know, it's amazing.

387
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:30,180
 Praise Jesus.

388
00:27:30,180 --> 00:27:35,700
 But not only that, He also gave me a greater faith than I ever had before.

389
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:38,540
 Like the crisis I went through, I had nothing.

390
00:27:38,540 --> 00:27:43,060
 I was a pastor at the time, I didn't have the faith to go through that crisis.

391
00:27:43,060 --> 00:27:46,000
 I didn't have it.

392
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:51,900
 And again, when we don't have it, we come to Jesus, "Jesus, I need you."

393
00:27:51,900 --> 00:27:57,020
 And so He, you know, through work, and again, this is a season, not a one moment, He gave

394
00:27:57,020 --> 00:28:00,660
 me a greater faith where I got to know God in a new way.

395
00:28:00,660 --> 00:28:04,100
 That He was much bigger than I knew He was.

396
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:06,940
 That He was more powerful than I knew He was.

397
00:28:06,940 --> 00:28:11,540
 That He was much more loving, much more present than I knew He was.

398
00:28:11,540 --> 00:28:20,660
 That was amazing.

399
00:28:20,660 --> 00:28:27,260
 So I experienced personal renewal, and one way that we can, or another way to describe

400
00:28:27,260 --> 00:28:31,540
 that is actually talking about personal revival.

401
00:28:31,540 --> 00:28:33,020
 So I want to say a little bit about revival.

402
00:28:33,020 --> 00:28:37,140
 So it can be personal revival, it can be community revival, it can be nationwide revival, and

403
00:28:37,140 --> 00:28:39,060
 national revival.

404
00:28:39,060 --> 00:28:46,300
 But one characteristic of revival is that it's not one moment.

405
00:28:46,300 --> 00:28:52,340
 It's actually a season where the Holy Spirit is poured out in a special way.

406
00:28:52,340 --> 00:28:53,340
 So that's the first thing.

407
00:28:53,340 --> 00:29:00,340
 And then the second thing is that this outpouring of the Holy Spirit, the season, that it brings

408
00:29:00,340 --> 00:29:03,740
 us, it's transformative.

409
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:08,740
 After that season, we're not the same people anymore.

410
00:29:08,740 --> 00:29:11,620
 You know, there is a new normal.

411
00:29:11,620 --> 00:29:15,660
 When God does a work in your life, there is a new normal.

412
00:29:15,660 --> 00:29:18,500
 He doesn't leave us where we're at.

413
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:21,980
 He does something new, something beautiful, something good.

414
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:24,900
 And that's a mark of true revival.

415
00:29:24,900 --> 00:29:30,500
 And as I was praying over us and thinking of what to share when I come back from sabbatic,

416
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:39,420
 I just really sensed that we're being invited for Jesus to bring personal revival in our

417
00:29:39,420 --> 00:29:40,420
 lives.

418
00:29:40,420 --> 00:29:47,820
 You know, that he wants to revive what is dead and make it alive, revive what is broken

419
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:51,100
 and bring newness and wholeness to it.

420
00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:54,860
 Now we can't force it, but we can ask for it.

421
00:29:54,860 --> 00:30:00,020
 God loves when we become thirsty, when we tell him where we need him to work and meet

422
00:30:00,020 --> 00:30:02,140
 us in our lives.

423
00:30:02,140 --> 00:30:07,060
 Now one thing that was so encouraging for me, on my trip, so I was on my sabbatical

424
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:11,740
 in Germany, in Hong Kong, in the US, my last thing that I was in the US, and I visited

425
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:12,980
 my host brother.

426
00:30:12,980 --> 00:30:18,380
 I lived with him in high school, my senior year, you know, rooming together then, and

427
00:30:18,380 --> 00:30:22,900
 then I was, my first three years in university, he was my roommate.

428
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:24,900
 So I hadn't seen him in 10 years.

429
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:28,900
 And he, after a week of spending time with each other, he's like, "Tim, you're not the

430
00:30:28,900 --> 00:30:32,180
 same person anymore."

431
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:36,060
 And it was not a negative, like, "Oh my gosh, you're not the same person anymore.

432
00:30:36,060 --> 00:30:37,060
 What happened to you?

433
00:30:37,060 --> 00:30:38,060
 What did he do to you in Hong Kong?"

434
00:30:38,060 --> 00:30:41,140
 No, it was like, "You're a different person."

435
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:44,580
 You know, he could tell.

436
00:30:44,580 --> 00:30:47,460
 It's this transformative work that God has done.

437
00:30:47,460 --> 00:30:49,320
 He has met me in my need.

438
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:50,620
 He has met me in my brokenness.

439
00:30:50,620 --> 00:30:53,580
 He has met me in my pain.

440
00:30:53,580 --> 00:30:55,300
 You know, and he can do that.

441
00:30:55,300 --> 00:30:56,300
 He can do it for me.

442
00:30:56,300 --> 00:30:57,300
 He can do it for you.

443
00:30:57,300 --> 00:31:07,260
 And as I was praying over us also this week, I just sensed that, you know, a lot of us,

444
00:31:07,260 --> 00:31:08,860
 we need a new normal.

445
00:31:08,860 --> 00:31:12,020
 Whatever's going on is not working.

446
00:31:12,020 --> 00:31:20,780
 We need the Holy Spirit to pour over our lives and do a new, a transformative work.

447
00:31:20,780 --> 00:31:26,300
 And so I want to invite the worship team to come up.

448
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:38,180
 And I, in a very simple way, but we also know it's not that simple, just invite you to actually

449
00:31:38,180 --> 00:31:44,460
 express your need, your longings that you are holding, that you are carrying in your

450
00:31:44,460 --> 00:31:48,020
 heart.

451
00:31:48,020 --> 00:31:53,020
 Maybe areas of pain or even maybe it's disappointment in yourself.

452
00:31:53,020 --> 00:31:56,140
 You're frustrated with yourself.

453
00:31:56,140 --> 00:31:58,700
 I just want to invite you to bring that to Jesus.

454
00:31:58,700 --> 00:31:59,980
 Say, "Jesus, I'm thirsty.

455
00:31:59,980 --> 00:32:02,700
 I need more of you in my life.

456
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:06,660
 I need you to meet me because I can't do it.

457
00:32:06,660 --> 00:32:09,060
 I'm at my wits' end.

458
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:13,460
 Will you meet me?"

459
00:32:13,460 --> 00:32:19,840
 And also just sense that we're invited to pray, "Holy Spirit, come.

460
00:32:19,840 --> 00:32:23,060
 Will you surround us with your presence?

461
00:32:23,060 --> 00:32:25,460
 Will you fill us, Holy Spirit?"

462
00:32:25,460 --> 00:32:29,800
 So we can just pray for this outpouring of the Holy Spirit.

463
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:36,700
 So as the worship team is going to gently play over us, I want to invite you to pray

464
00:32:36,700 --> 00:32:43,020
 right now, just to come to Jesus and just to cry out to him to express the longing of

465
00:32:43,020 --> 00:32:44,020
 your heart.

466
00:32:44,020 --> 00:32:47,100
 And just say, "Jesus, I need you.

467
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:51,020
 Holy Spirit, I need you in my life.

468
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:52,020
 Will you meet me?

469
00:32:52,020 --> 00:32:55,660
 Will you give me that water, that drink?

470
00:32:55,660 --> 00:32:58,900
 Will you quench my thirst?"

471
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:02,620
 Because he's the only one who can do it.

472
00:33:02,620 --> 00:33:08,580
 So I encourage you to express it on your own in prayer, but you're also welcome to turn

473
00:33:08,580 --> 00:33:11,700
 to somebody and just pray with them.

474
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:13,500
 So let's lean into that right now.

475
00:33:13,500 --> 00:33:19,300
 And I'm going to just start us off with a prayer, but you continue with your own prayers.

476
00:33:19,300 --> 00:33:23,380
 So Holy Spirit, come.

477
00:33:23,380 --> 00:33:27,260
 Lord, we are desperate.

478
00:33:27,260 --> 00:33:29,620
 We need you.

479
00:33:29,620 --> 00:33:34,580
 We need you in our lives.

480
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:37,260
 They're part of our lives that are dead.

481
00:33:37,260 --> 00:33:40,300
 Will you come and revive us?

482
00:33:40,300 --> 00:33:42,900
 There is pain that's just too much for us to carry.

483
00:33:42,900 --> 00:33:46,660
 Will you come and heal that pain?

484
00:33:46,660 --> 00:33:49,860
 There is hopelessness where we've given up.

485
00:33:49,860 --> 00:33:55,580
 Will you revive that hope?

486
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:58,660
 There's addiction.

487
00:33:58,660 --> 00:34:01,460
 Will you break that power of addiction of our lives?

488
00:34:01,460 --> 00:34:08,140
 Will you remove us and give us freedom?

489
00:34:08,140 --> 00:34:10,740
 Thank you, Jesus.

490
00:34:10,740 --> 00:34:12,540
 Thank you, Jesus.

491
00:34:12,540 --> 00:34:13,380
 Let's continue to pray.

492
00:34:13,380 --> 00:34:16,740
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

